    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear emphasis on aggressive baserunning and high-upside matchups. **Kyle Tucker** (81.01) stands as our premier play, benefiting from a favorable wind-out environment and a high-probability matchup against Jack Leiter, whose command profile elevates **Tucker**\u2019s base projection significantly. Similarly, **Jackson Merrill** (75.27) and **Gunnar Henderson** (69.67) are cornerstone starters today; **Merrill** benefits from an exploitable, slow-delivering pitcher that reinforces our prioritization of stolen base potential, while **Henderson** overcomes a difficult arm in Logan Webb due to the potent combination of a massive park factor and his elite leadoff order placement. **Luis Robert Jr.** (63.03) also makes the cut as a high-efficiency start, leveraging a strong platoon edge despite the presence of a quick-working catcher.\n\nThe most difficult exclusion of the day was **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (50.63), who fell just shy of the threshold. While his raw base projection remains high, he is currently being squeezed out by the concentration of better platoon-adjusted options and lineup efficiency scores in our utility and corner infield slots. Meanwhile, we remain cautious regarding the risks inherent in our \"Lineup Pending\" designations\u2014specifically for **Drake Baldwin** and **Nasim Nunez**\u2014as any shift in the batting order could trigger a rapid re-evaluation of their efficiency scores. We are also monitoring the matchup for **Heliot Ramos** (56.05) and **Andy Pages** (63.51); while **Pages** is a strong play thanks to his speed profile and favorable wind conditions, the bottom-of-the-order placement for both players remains the primary downward pressure on their daily projections.",
